</span>): <span class=s><b>4:32am</b></span><tr><td id="pb51438252" class="l w pd"><div class=narrow>Na only stealing you see, stealing na jara.<br>Na suicide de reign, na.<br>Bubu is a curse!<br><br>Incase your head de turn when u read plenty plenty materials or, plus you eye de spin, so for that, you no been fit read more text book above, make I give u certain important quotes from de book where go help u sabi weting de man yarn<br>1. <br>YOUR recent comments about President Muhammadu Buhari is eliciting reactions from different quarters. Would you say Nigeria is on a reverse gear?<br>At least if it is not on a reverse gear it is on a standstill.<br>2. <br>There is this claim that the president has been hijacked by a clique. As someone who has worked with him closely, can this be true? Do you see him as someone that can be hijacked?<br>What I expect the president to do is to come out clean. The  other time, the president said anybody  accusing top members of his government should come up with his or her evidence  if such person had any .<br><br>The following day, Sahara Reporters came out clean on a minister, divulged  all his properties, bank account in the United States. Every sensible man would have thought that the president would query such a<br><br>minister or at worst ask him to step aside until proper investigation is carried out on how he came about those properties and money in his account. But that was not done.<br>3.<br>You did observe that Nigeria is standing still, do you see the situation remaining that way till the end of this tenure?<br><br>You mean you can change a 74-year-old man? Nigerian should know that they have to take whatever the president decides to do when he decides to do it.<br><br>4. <br>Are you likely move to another party if it becomes increasingly clear that you are unwelcome in APC or if a party with better prospects emerge?<br><br>The issue about government is not what you get personally. What is it that the government will do for the society, for the country? That is the issue. When this government will fail is if it can’t deliver. Show me the promise made by Buhari that has been fulfilled. That he would make a litre of petrol N45?  We will ask him when the time comes. He said he would make a naira equivalent to a dollar, we will ask him. Then we will know whether he lives by his word.</div><p class=s> <b id="lpt51438252">33 Likes </b> <b id='shb51438252'> 3 Shares</b><tr><td class="bold l pu"><a name="51438272"></a><a name="msg51438272"></a><a name="3489685.12"></a><a href="/3489685/under-buhari-people-just-stealing#51438272">Re: Under Buhari, People Are Just Stealing Left, Right And Centre —buba Galadima</a> by <a href="/freeze001" class=user>freeze001</a>(<span class="f">f</span>): <span class=s><b>4:37am</b></span><tr><td id="pb51438272" class="l w pd"><div class=narrow><blockquote><a href=/post/51437861><b>sarrki</a></b>:<br>Baba Buba fear God <br><br>Criticize constructively </blockquote><br>What is not constructive about what he has said? Person no dey talk true una accept am quietly as true den find solution to problem? God forbid! Which fear of God pass d swear wey him swear on top koran?</div><p class=s> <b id="lpt51438272">32 Likes </b> <b id='shb51438272'> 3 Shares</b><tr><td class="bold l pu"><a name="51438281"></a><a name="msg51438281"></a><a name="3489685.13"></a><a href="/3489685/under-buhari-people-just-stealing#51438281">Re: Under Buhari, People Are Just Stealing Left, Right And Centre —buba Galadima</a> by <a href="/atiku2019" class=user>Atiku2019</a>: <span class=s><b>4:40am</b></span><tr><td id="pb51438281" class="l w pd"><div class=narrow>Buhari is Incompetent. Dazzol<br><br>
